00:33:40.010 --> 00:33:46.980
And we saw the price of gas
spike like $0.40 in many

00:33:46.980 --> 00:33:49.440
states a few months ago, just
because of one refinery fire

00:33:49.440 --> 00:33:51.370
that was, I'm sure, thousands of
miles away from most of the

00:33:51.370 --> 00:33:52.466
people affected

00:33:52.466 --> 00:33:56.760
I think there's lots of evidence
now that the stuff

00:33:56.760 --> 00:33:58.970
happening half a world away
really does affect your life

00:33:58.970 --> 00:34:00.500
on a day to day basis.

00:34:00.500 --> 00:34:02.990
I guess the better question is,
is there so much happening

00:34:02.990 --> 00:34:05.840
that there's really no hope
that the well-informed lay

00:34:05.840 --> 00:34:08.639
person like you or me can
actually understand the

00:34:08.639 --> 00:34:11.639
financial situation in China
well enough to make wise

00:34:11.639 --> 00:34:15.420
decisions based on that,
so why bother?

00:34:15.420 --> 00:34:16.790
I don't have a better
rebuttal for that.

00:34:16.790 --> 00:34:18.560
I'm afraid we're getting to the
point where that is true.

00:34:18.560 --> 00:34:25.250
And does democracy have less
value in a world where a voter

00:34:25.250 --> 00:34:27.590
really can't be well informed
about all the important issues

00:34:27.590 --> 00:34:27.800
that matter?

00:34:27.800 --> 00:34:28.719
I don't know.

00:34:28.719 --> 00:34:29.969
It's an interesting question.

00:34:34.070 --> 00:34:36.140
Yeah, go ahead?

00:34:36.140 --> 00:34:37.330
AUDIENCE: So thank
you for coming.

00:34:37.330 --> 00:34:39.670
I actually remember watching
your historic run on

00:34:39.670 --> 00:34:41.739
"Jeopardy" with my roommate
at the time.

00:34:41.739 --> 00:34:45.179
We would tune in every day and
watch and kind of like hope

00:34:45.179 --> 00:34:47.820
that we're going to watch the
day that Ken Jennings gets

00:34:47.820 --> 00:34:50.210
defeated, finally.

00:34:50.210 --> 00:34:52.330
KEN JENNINGS: So let me
get this straight.

00:34:52.330 --> 00:34:55.526
I've got like the best
job I've ever had.

00:34:55.526 --> 00:34:59.350
I'm making like $50K an
hour or something.

00:34:59.350 --> 00:35:01.240
And yet kids all over college
campuses, all over America,

00:35:01.240 --> 00:35:03.340
are hoping I get fired.

00:35:03.340 --> 00:35:04.940
AUDIENCE: We were fascinated,
yeah every day.

00:35:04.940 --> 00:35:09.540
I remember there was like an
internet rumor that today was

00:35:09.540 --> 00:35:10.640
the day that Ken lost.

00:35:10.640 --> 00:35:12.507
And then the H&amp;R Block question
came up and we were

00:35:12.507 --> 00:35:15.680
like no way, he knows this.

00:35:15.680 --> 00:35:18.700
KEN JENNINGS: So not only are
you hoping I lose, you thought

00:35:18.700 --> 00:35:21.670
it was a super easy question?

00:35:21.670 --> 00:35:24.180
AUDIENCE: Well, to
be fair, we did.

00:35:24.180 --> 00:35:26.010
Anyway my question is, I've
always wondered this, does

00:35:26.010 --> 00:35:29.540
Alex Trebek actually know the
answers to the questions?

00:35:29.540 --> 00:35:29.970
KEN JENNINGS: Alex?

00:35:29.970 --> 00:35:32.820
You know, it's funny.

00:35:32.820 --> 00:35:37.760
I think "Jeopardy" is really,
the core viewership is college

00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:40.183
students and old people.

00:35:40.183 --> 00:35:42.980
I get the feeling nobody with
a job actually watches

00:35:42.980 --> 00:35:46.220
"Jeopardy." And it's great
because the fact that the

00:35:46.220 --> 00:35:47.850
audience skews to old means
that I don't get

00:35:47.850 --> 00:35:48.470
recognized any more.

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:53.020
Most of the people who saw me
on the show are now dead or

00:35:53.020 --> 00:35:55.400
they graduated.

00:35:55.400 --> 00:35:57.060
Alex is a smart guy.

00:35:57.060 --> 00:35:58.310
He's a big reader.

00:36:00.740 --> 00:36:01.767
I've talked to him.

00:36:01.767 --> 00:36:03.320
And he hosts the National
Geographic Bee.

00:36:03.320 --> 00:36:04.460
And that's because he's
a true believer.

00:36:04.460 --> 00:36:06.470
He's got a basement full of
"National Geographic"s going

00:36:06.470 --> 00:36:07.290
back 50 years.

00:36:07.290 --> 00:36:11.070
And basically he's your grandpa
watching History

00:36:11.070 --> 00:36:13.330
Channel documentaries
